;
NUMBER 1689
NAME Inner Sea, Hidden Cove
DARKNESS
ASTRAL
*DESCRIPTION_START
You gaze in wonder at the stark, simple beauty of the shoreline. The rock
walls completely surround the back and sides of the cove with an almost
overpowering presence. It is not hard to imagine how this small beach of
fine, black sand has gone un-noticed all these years. The black walls extend
for hundreds of feet straight up and glisten in the light with the slick
wetness of sea spray. The only mark in their natural ruggedness is the
stairway carved along one wall. The water itself is quite calm here, but the
jagged outcroppings of rock along the shore prevent any boats from docking
here. Several tide pools and a steaming natural spring are off to one side of
the cove, where high tide would cover them for much of the day.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
EXIT U 529

; Pool
ITEM 0 736
; Water
ITEM 1 1062
; Spring
ITEM 2 1772 ADJ1=42

IFTOUCH 1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER Which water do you mean, the tide pool or the spring?
ENDIF

IFPREVERB LOOK 0
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You gaze idly into the tidepool for a moment, transfixed by the various forms
  ECHO PLAYER of life which make their home here. The starfish, sea urchins and minnows
  ECHO PLAYER seem blissfully unaware that they are no longer within the ocean itself. As
  ECHO PLAYER you lean closer for a better look, your shadow startles a school of minnows.
  ECHO OTHERS %N stares into the tidepool.
ENDIF
;
IFPREVERB TAKE 0
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You pull up your sleeve and reach into the chilly water. After a few moments,
  ECHO PLAYER you are able to retrieve a starfish, inspecting it briefly before returning
  ECHO PLAYER it to the water.
  ECHO OTHERS %N pulls up %h sleeve and reaches into the tide pool. After a few moments, %s produces a starfish, inspecting briefly before returning it to the water.
ENDIF
;
IFPREVERB SLAP 0
  CLEARVERB
  IFVAR PLRSINROOM = 2
    ECHO PLAYER You playfully splash around in the water
    ECHO OTHERS %N playfully splashes you with the water!
  ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER You playfully splash around in the water.
    ECHO OTHERS %N splashes around in the water.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
;
IFPREVERB GO 0
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You step into the cold tide pool and sit down at its edge.
  ECHO OTHERS %N steps into the tide pool and sits down at its edge.
  POSITION SIT
  EQUAL FLAG1 919
ENDIF
;
IFPREVERB LOOK 2
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO OTHERS %N peers into the bubbling spring. When %s turns away, you notice that %h face is wet with condensation.
  ECHO PLAYER You look carefully into the depths of the natural spring, in hopes of seeing
  ECHO PLAYER the bottom through the bubbling water. As you lean over the spring, warm
  ECHO PLAYER condensation forms on your face and neck.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB TOUCH 2
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO OTHERS %N pulls up %h sleeve and tentatively thrusts %h hand into the bubbling water.
  ECHO PLAYER You pull up your sleeve and reach into the bubbling water. To your surprise,
  ECHO PLAYER the water is comfortably warm; about the same temperature as the hot tub in
  ECHO PLAYER the saloon.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB GO 2
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You slowly lower yourself into the hot spring, and take a seat on one of the natural shelves around the edge.
  ECHO OTHERS %N slowly lowers %iself into the hot spring and takes a seat on one of the natural shelves around the edge.
  POSITION SIT
  EQUAL FLAG1 929
ENDIF
IFPREVERB STAND -1
  IFVAR FLAG1 = 919
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER You step out of the pool.
    ECHO OTHERS %N steps out of the pool.
    POSITION STAND
  ENDIF
  IFVAR FLAG1 = 929
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER You pull yourself out of the stream and shiver in the cold air.
    ECHO OTHERS %N pulls %iself out of the bubbling stream.
    POSITION STAND
  ENDIF
  EQUAL FLAG1 0
ENDIF
