NUMBER 529
NAME Inner Sea, water's edge
*DESCRIPTION_START
Waves gently lap over a large, rusted anchor stuck in the sand at the water's
edge. A thick chain leads into the sea from the anchor. The anchor, judging by
its worn condition, has been sitting here for some time. The relentless waves
have exposed an opening in the rocks which leads down into darkness.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT E 528
EXIT SW 530
; Anchor
ITEM 0 402 ADJ1=272
; Sand
ITEM 1 413
; Opening
ITEM 2 72 VAL2=978
IFPREVERB CLIMB 0
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You hop over the anchor and land on rocky terrain...
  ECHO OTHERS %N hops over the rusty anchor...
  AFFECT 1689
  ECHO OTHERS %N climbs in.
  AFFECT 529
  MOVE 1689
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 1688
NAME Exotic Pets of Andor Ltd.
INDOOR_FLOOR
*DESCRIPTION_START
Cages upon cages of madly concieved animals line the walls of this extremely
noisy shoppe. A large glass tank filled with various aquatic life rests
against the far wall. Behind the wooden counter, two men with identical
moustachioed visages argue about pricing and which animals should be carried,
and which should be killed on sight. A manuscript lists the pets currently
for sale.
*DESCRIPTION_END
; Door to Hadan Kentarus
